Sentencas: A new A-site excessive strategy is reported to improve performance of layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).

Sentencas: A new A-site excessive Gd1+x Ba1+xCo2O5+delta layered perovskite is investigated as cathode materials for IT-SOFCs.

Sentencas: With an excess of A-site content, the crystal lattice and the thermal expansion coefficient increase slightly.

Sentencas: The oxygen nonstoichiometry (d) increases, while the oxygen vacancy decreases by defect chemistry analysis.
Titulo: A new A-site excessive strategy to improve performance of layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A-site excessive Gd1.05Ba1.05Co2O5+delta (GBC1.05) is well compatible with Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-delta at 1000 degrees C for 10 h. The electrical conductivity of GBC1.05 increases dramatically owing to the higher concentration of electron hole and the lower oxygen vacancy concentration.
Titulo: A new A-site excessive strategy to improve performance of layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance towards oxygen reduction reaction can be enhanced from 0.246 Omega cm(2) to 0.146 Omega cm(2) by introducing A-site excessive content of Gd and Ba.
Titulo: A new A-site excessive strategy to improve performance of layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Consequently, GBC1.05 cathode exhibits a good cell performance of 830 mW cm (2) at 800 degrees C, indicating that A-site excessive Gd1.05Ba1.05Co2O5+delta layered perovskite is a potential cathode material for IT-SOFCs due to its high electrochemical performance.
